Experiment performed at flight path
FP14 at the LANSCE- Lujan Center at Los Alamos
National Laboratory using DANCE array.
Gamma rays were detected by DANCE - a 4Pi
calorimetric gamma-ray detector. It consists of 160
BaF2 crystals, each about 0.75 l in volume and 15 cm
long. The face of each crystal is 17 cm from the
sample center.

Experiment performed at flight path
FP14 at the LANSCE- Lujan Center at Los Alamos
National Laboratory using DANCE array.
Neutrons were produced by bombardinng
tungsten target with 800 MeV protons.The resulting
neutrons were cooled down in a water moderator and
collimated into flight path 14. Neutron energy range
was from subthermal neutron up to 100 keV.
Time of flight was used to determine incident
neutron energy
The 173Lu target was produced using successively,
proton irradiation of Hf sample at the Isotope
Production Facility. A 49.12 g natural Hf sample was
irradiated by a 93 MeV energy proton beam for 14
days. After several months of cooling time, the
irradiated sample was treated chemically to separate Lu
from Hf and beta decays products. Two samples were
prepared and purified from Lu beta decay products.
The final target isotopic composition for two samples
was          Target 1        Target 2

The Lu solution was finally deposited by electro-
deposition on a 2.5 mu-m thick titanium foil.
